{"title":"Regulatory Article (RA) 5805: responsibilities of the holders of a military type certificate (MTC) and MAA design organization approvals (MRP 21 Subpart A)","public_updated_at":"2016-08-25T11:00:17Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\">\n<p>The purpose of Regulatory Articles (<abbr title=\"Regulatory Articles\">RA</abbr>) is to provide the framework of policy, rules, directives, standards, processes and the associated direction, advice and guidance, which governs military aviation activity and against which air safety is assessed. The regulator develops regulations in response to applicable UK law, <abbr title=\"Ministry of Defence\">MOD</abbr> needs, legal changes and recommendations resulting from both assurance or investigation functions.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"related-information\">Related information:</h3>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/maa-regulatory-publications\"><abbr title=\"Military Aviation Authority\">MAA</abbr> regulatory publications</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/maa-regulatory-publications-overarching-documents\">Overarching documents</a></li>\n  <li>Regulatory Articles (<abbr title=\"Regulatory Articles\">RA</abbr>)\n    <ul>\n      <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/1000-series-general-regulations-gen\">1000 series (<abbr title=\"General Regulations\">GEN</abbr>)</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/2000-series-flying-regulations-fly\">2000 series (<abbr title=\"Flying Regulations\">FLY</abbr>)</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/3000-series-air-traffic-management-regulations-atm\">3000 series (<abbr title=\"Air Traffic Management Regulations\">ATM</abbr>)</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/4000-series-continuing-airworthiness-engineering-regulations-cae\">4000 series (<abbr title=\"Continuing Airworthiness Engineering Regulations\">CAE</a